The paper deals with identity testing for high-dimensional distributions, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of differential privacy suggests a focus on machine learning and privacy (cs.LG), while the construction of testers involves computational complexity (cs.CR) and the reduction to univariate testing involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DM).
